subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia
(Genital preparation № OG–006-1998) (
Figs 11–15
). Tegumen-uncus complex relatively broad; scopula androconialis well-developed, about 0.4 times as long as tegumen-uncus complex (
Fig. 11
); crista gnathi medialis long and broad; crista gnati lateralis subcordiform, about half as long as and slightly narrower than crista gnathi medialis (
Fig. 11
); valva (
Fig. 12
) trapeziform-ovoid, crista sacculi oblique, dual, covered with apically pointed setae anteriorly and flat-topped ones posteriorly; caudal part of row of setae bent towards ventral margin; saccus (
Fig. 13
) narrow, rounded basally, long, about twice as long as vinculum; aedeagus (
Fig. 14
) thin, straight, nearly as long as valva; vesica with numerous small cornuti (
Fig. 15
).
